  "text": "There are a number of factors that could affect the AC breakdown performance of natural ester during the gelling process. As seen in Fig. 5 , severe deformation of the gel at the late stage could form micro voids inside the sample, which poses a negative effect on the breakdown voltage [CITATION_1] . At the same time, some other mechanisms known to influence AC breakdown strength, e.g. particle motion [CITATION_2] , become less significant due to the increased viscosity of natural ester during the gelling process. The increasing viscosity could also make the formation of discharge channel more difficult. In addition, although the acidity increases significantly, those acid by-products might be mainly high molecular weight acids, which are less polar and have less negative impact on the breakdown voltage. There is a trade-off between all these factors, which results in a stabilized AC breakdown performance of natural esters during the gelling process.",
